I"¨<p>This is kind of silly, but as I have been putting together my <a href="/multivar">multivariable calc notes/cheatsheet</a>, Kramdownâ€™s default LaTeX renderer, \({\KaTeX}\), by default centers any \({\KaTeX}\) written without text surrounding it (i.e. it handled inline fine, but any non-inline \({\KaTeX}\) automatically became centered display \({\KaTeX}\)). And I wanted it to be left-aligned.</p>

<p>I went through a lot of documentation to see how I could adjust my <code class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><span class="n">_config</span><span class="p">.</span><span class="n">yml</span></code> to evoke something like \({\KaTeX}\)â€™s <code class="language-python highlighter-rouge"><span class="n">fleqn</span></code> option<sup id="fnref:1" role="doc-noteref"><a href="#fn:1" class="footnote">1</a></sup> but had no success. Ultimately, adding this to my custom CSS worked for me:</p>

